textAfterTable: Tom Brady Fantasy Analysis Brady's 4-game suspension upheld Commissioner Roger Goodell has upheld Patriot QB Tom Brady's 4-game suspension. This story is far from over, though.  Multiple sources have reported that Brady is expected to take the decision to court.  That process could take months.  And Brady would be able to play while the legal process plays out.  For now, fantasy owners should continue to assume Brady will miss 4 games at some point this season, but this remains a fluid situation.  Brady's MFL10 ADP has held steady in the early 10th round throughout July. Full Story Jul 28, 2015 Brady suspension could go to court ABC News' Ryan Smith hears that the NFLPA is prepared to go to court if Patriots QB Tom Brady's appeal results in a suspension for any games.  Brady is currently looking at a 4-game ban, and the odds of that being wiped down to 0 seem slim.  If the situation is taken to court, it could become a long process.  And it's possible that Brady is allowed to play while the legal process plays out.  We'll continue to keep a close eye on this story.  Brady's ADP is sitting in the early 10th round as the 10th QB off the board in recent MFL10 drafts.
